<TITLE> SQ Chy faces arrest warrant </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 10 (bdnews24.com)A Tangail court issued an arrest warrant against BNP lawmaker Salahddin Qader Chowdhury on Thursday in a defamation case for making a disparaging comment about Sheikh Mujibur Rahman at the National Press Club on Aug 13. Judge Waies Al Qurunee, of Tangail judicial magistrates court, issued the warrant, after the case was filed by Tangail Jubo League vice-president Abdur Rahim on Aug 19. Chowdhury was reported to have said the assassination of Sheikh Mujib and members of his family had been "inevitable", a remark that sparked widespread condemnation throughout the country. Three other cases have been filed against Chowdhury on the same charge in Magura, Khulna and Narail. bdnews24.c
